{"key":"processedPost-9531257","value":{"id":9531257,"first":9530443,"last":9607261,"when":1230911956,"utime":"01/02/09 05:59 PM","content":"Make the holes about 2 inches apart (5 cm) on all six sides.&nbsp; Use a 1/4\" drill bit(6mm).&nbsp; If you drill the holes too large it will require much more frequent misting.&nbsp; Don't use a 3/8\" drill bit.&nbsp; A 3/8\" hole has more than twice as much area as a 1/4\" hole.<br /><br />If you make it as directed, the perlite won't dry out for at least 6 weeks, which is plenty of time for a cropping cycle, at which time you rinse, drain, and return the perlite to service.<br />RR","title":"Re: How many holes do I need in my shotgun terrarium?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}